  "chapter": {
    "number": 8,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Basket of Summer Fruit"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "This is what the Lord GOD showed me: I saw a basket of summer fruit.",
          {
            "noteId": 1321
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "“Amos, what do you see?” He asked.",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "“A basket of summer fruit,” I replied.",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "So the LORD said to me, “The end has come for My people Israel; I will no longer spare them.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "“In that day,” declares the Lord GOD, “the songs",
          {
            "noteId": 1322
          },
          "of the temple",
          {
            "noteId": 1323
          },
          "will turn to wailing. Many will be the corpses, strewn in silence everywhere!”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hear this, you who trample the needy,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who do away with the poor of the land,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "asking, “When will the New Moon be over,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that we may sell grain?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "When will the Sabbath end,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that we may market wheat?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Let us reduce the ephah and increase the shekel;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1324
          },
          {
            "text": "let us cheat with dishonest scales.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let us buy the poor with silver",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the needy for a pair of sandals,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "selling even the chaff with the wheat!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "The LORD has sworn by the Pride of Jacob:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I will never forget any of their deeds.",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Will not the land quake for this,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all its dwellers mourn?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "All of it will swell like the Nile;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it will surge and then subside",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "like the Nile in Egypt.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And in that day,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the Lord GOD,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will make the sun go down at noon,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will darken the earth in the daytime.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will turn your feasts into mourning",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and all your songs into lamentation.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will cause everyone to wear sackcloth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and every head to be shaved.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will make it like a time of mourning for an only son,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and its outcome like a bitter day.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, the days are coming,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the Lord GOD,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "when I will send a famine on the land—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "not a famine of bread or a thirst for water,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a famine of hearing the words of the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "People will stagger from sea to sea",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and roam from north to east,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "seeking the word of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but they will not find it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In that day the lovely young women—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the young men as well—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "will faint from thirst.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Those who swear by the guilt of Samaria",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and say, ‘As surely as your god lives, O Dan,’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "or, ‘As surely as the way",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1325
          },
          {
            "text": "of Beersheba lives’—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will fall, never to rise again.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
